{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":312626,"duration_api_ms":264819,"num_turns":31,"result":"All 1163 tests pass (351 + 128 + 1 + 683). \n\n```json\n{\n  \"change_summary\": \"Eliminated the duplicate journal detail structs by moving the canonical owned types (`StartJournalDetails`, `CompletionJournalDetails`) into model.rs with `Serialize + Deserialize + Clone + deny_unknown_fields`, and removing the duplicate definitions from fs.rs. Both the render path (model.rs `render_*` functions) and the parse path (fs.rs `parse()` via `serde_json::from_str`) now use the exact same struct definition, making field-set drift structurally impossible — adding a field to the render function requires updating the struct, which automatically updates the parse path. The private borrowed `StartJournalDetailsPayload<'a>` and `CompletionJournalDetailsPayload<'a>` types were removed since the render functions now construct and serialize the owned types directly. The fs.rs `impl` blocks for `parse()`, `merge()`, and `render()` remain as inherent impls on the model types (valid within the same crate).\",\n  \"outstanding_risks\": [\n    \"Pre-existing formatting drift in tests/unit/agent_execution_test.rs is unrelated to these changes but will appear in cargo fmt --check across the full workspace.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added public owned StartJournalDetails and CompletionJournalDetails structs to model.rs with Serialize + Deserialize + Clone + deny_unknown_fields. These are the single canonical definition of the journal detail field sets\",\n      \"order\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Updated render_start_journal_details and render_completion_journal_details in model.rs to construct and serialize the new owned types instead of the private borrowed payload types. Removed the now-unnecessary StartJournalDetailsPayload<'a> and CompletionJournalDetailsPayload<'a> private structs\",\n      \"order\": 2,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Removed duplicate StartJournalDetails and CompletionJournalDetails struct definitions from fs.rs. Added imports of the model types. Kept the impl blocks for parse(), merge(), render() as same-crate inherent impls on the model types\",\n      \"order\": 3,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Updated round-trip test doc comments in fs.rs to reflect that both render and parse now use the same canonical struct from model.rs, making drift structurally impossible rather than test-detectable\",\n      \"order\": 4,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Ran cargo test (1163 total: 351 lib + 128 integration + 1 doc + 683 unit, 0 failed), cargo clippy -- -D warnings (clean), cargo fmt --check on modified files (clean)\",\n      \"order\": 5,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"validation_evidence\": [\n    \"cargo test: 1163 total tests passed (351 lib + 128 integration + 1 doc + 683 unit), 0 failed\",\n    \"cargo clippy -- -D warnings: no warnings or errors\",\n    \"cargo fmt --check: fs.rs and model.rs clean; only pre-existing formatting diffs in unrelated tests/unit/agent_execution_test.rs\",\n    \"Structural guarantee: render_start_journal_details constructs StartJournalDetails (model.rs:371), and StartJournalDetails::parse deserializes into the same type (fs.rs:2280-2281). Adding a field to the render function requires adding it to the struct, which automatically makes the parse path handle it — drift is a compile error, not a test failure\",\n    \"deny_unknown_fields on both types provides runtime defense-in-depth: if any code path were to somehow produce JSON with extra fields, deserialization would fail immediately rather than silently discarding them\",\n    \"Existing round-trip tests (start_journal_details_round_trips_with_model_render, completion_journal_details_round_trips_w